To live in a declining city, yet make one's home in virtue;
To retire from the ways of the world, and cultivate the waters;
To rule a country with art, and govern as a wandering scholar;
To be prosperous under heaven, and have a name that endures;
To be tranquil and at peace, with clouds and winds in harmony;
To govern the people, or not to cultivate the fields;
To be a vagabond, yet have a heart's resolve;
To live in a peaceful land, yet not observe the virtues;
To be wise, yet not understand the water's wisdom;
To be virtuous, yet rule the wilds with wind.
To have faith, yet exalt the country;
My subjects, I am still a student of the Way.
